<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Fornost</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-04-25 12:34:13</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>AAAAAAACCCCCKKKKK..........<BR>
<BR>
That's what I have to say about the not equipable by Clerics thing....this is the next best thing to the Pearl Kedge Totem dammit and a neck slot that gives wis and AC both in quantity....damn it damn it damn it...oh well time to twink the ranger I guess.  <BR>
<BR>
About the casters whining about them not being able to wear it...here's the low down....a torque is an ancient Celtic neck-piece and frankly one of the only metalic armour pieces that celts made and wore(not really armour but jewellery)  It consists of many small strands of metal braided together to resemble a steel cable bent around the neck(ends don't clasp together) and usually having an animal totem on either end that end facing each other in front of the larynx.  The diameter of the cable section usually is close to or more than an inch and the totems are bulky and heavy.  This is a burly piece not a fine piece of jewellery more fitted for a caster(like a BiM.)  Based on it's origin I would argue that this piece would be best suited for a Barbarian and more specifically a Shaman..but this is just my opinion.  </font></td></tr></table>
